<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE PRESS AND 'GROUP-THINK' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Spin is merely another word for bias, something journalists pretend they don't 
have. Bias is nothing new; it's just more uniform and more obvious these days, 
thanks to poorly educated reporters and editors. 
</P>
<P>
And since these fledgling reporters have no sense of history, today is the 
beginning of mankind for them. 
</P>
<P>
That's why they're so gullible, so addicted to socialistic causes, and so naive 
as the think anyone cares about their shallow opinions. 
</P>
<P>
For the press -- especially the TV press -- one swallow does indeed make a 
thousand summers and molehills are daily to be made mountains. 
</P>
<P>
MIKE COLBY 
</P>
<P>
Covina 
</P>
</TEXT>
