<HEADLINE>
<P>
TOBACCO TAX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In his letter printed Aug. 11, A.J. Tobias delights in his circumvention of the 
state tobacco tax, gloating that "the creators of the tobacco tax must think we 
smokers are a bunch of dum-dums." 
</P>
<P>
Smoking has been proven to cause cancer, emphysema and birth defects and is the 
leading cause of preventable death in the country. Each time a smoker lights 
up, be it a cigarette, cigar or pipe, he has proven himself to be the dum-dum 
indeed. 
</P>
<P>
JOEL PERRY 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
