<HEADLINE>
<P>
NO WELCOME MAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Golly, I didn't realize that the state of Washington is becoming a private 
sector of our nation ("Welcome to Seattle . . . Now Go Home," by Ann Japenga, 
Aug. 24 ). Will we be required to have a visa to cross their border? Proof of 
inoculations? Will this apply only to Californians? If so, what actually 
constitutes a "Californian"? 
</P>
<P>
Gee, I'm third-generation, but the vast majority of people I've known and met 
weren't even born in this state. Does having a California license plate 
automatically make one a native? When did the welcome mat get trashed that was 
spread before us in 1962 when Seattle held the World's Fair? The color of our 
money hasn't changed. 
</P>
<P>
LaMAE NORMINGTON, Anaheim 
</P>
