<HEADLINE>
<P>
ABORTION AND BIOLOGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Julian P. Donahue's Aug. 20 letter defending a pro-abortion cartoon by Jules 
Feiffer must be correct because he is a biologist and curator of insects, 
right? 
</P>
<P>
It would be interesting to see Mr. Donahue's face the day it is decided that, 
like his "genetically unfit individuals," curators of insects "aren't making a 
meaningful contribution to society" and are "just taking up space." Should they 
then be eliminated, as individuals are eliminated in abortion and euthanasia? 
</P>
<P>
Donahue says it's a matter of "just good biology." I think not. Just bad 
philosophy. 
</P>
<P>
MARK RITTER 
</P>
<P>
Ontario 
</P>
