<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAVING KFAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Matthew B. Topper's Aug. 20 letter is right in saying the conversion of KFAC to 
a rock station would be cultural vandalism. 
</P>
<P>
What can be done? As an ex-New Yorker, I see two options: (1) The City of Los 
Angeles could condemn KFAC under the eminent domain laws and operate the 
station itself; this sounds far-fetched, but the City of New York has been 
successfully operating WNYC for decades. (2) The Los Angeles Times could buy 
and operate a classical station itself. This is precisely the relation that the 
New York Times has with WQXR, which is primarily a classical station but also 
serves as a worthwhile extension of journalistic function. 
</P>
<P>
DANA F. SUTTON 
</P>
<P>
Corona 
</P>
</TEXT>
