<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIVORCE ON THE RISE IN SOUTH KOREA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SEOUL, South Korea 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Divorce is on the rise and infidelity is blamed in nearly half of the cases, 
according to court statistics released Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Of the 20,345 cases filed with the Supreme Court in 1988, about 90% involved 
couples with children and 47.4% cited infidelity for the breakup. 
</P>
<P>
For this year, the court said 27,778 cases already had been filed by the end of 
July. 
</P>
