<HEADLINE>
<P>
MUSICAL AIRPORTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I'm convinced. I've been convinced ever since the first time I landed a jet 
fighter at Lindbergh Field (1959)! San Diego does need a better and much safer 
international airport. 
</P>
<P>
There's a logical solution staring us in the face. The "center of population" 
of those who fly with the airlines is on the north side of San Diego, not on 
the south side, near Brown Field. But, the Navy needs and will not give up 
Miramar Naval Air Station. 
</P>
<P>
So, let's do the obvious: use the money for a new international airport to 
upgrade and construct a new "Miramar NAS" at (and perhaps just north of) Brown 
Field. Build new family housing, the "works." 
</P>
<P>
Then the only logical site for our new airport becomes available, Miramar. 
</P>
<P>
CARROLL NJUST 
</P>
<P>
Fallbrook 
</P>
