<TEXT>
<P>
Mr. Nickerson set a stakes record in winning his third consecutive race, a 2 
1/4-length victory in the $113,000 Boojum Handicap at Belmont Park in Elmont, 
N.Y. 
</P>
<P>
Mr. Nickerson, ridden by Craig Perret, covered six furlongs in 1:08 1/5, 
two-fifths of a second better than the time posted by Soy Numero Uno in 1976 
and matched by King's Swan in 1986. 
</P>
