<HEADLINE>
<P>
TRAVEL PROGRAMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Costa Rica, El Salvador and Guatemala will be among the regions explored by 
travel photographer and lecturer Mort Loveman in a slide presentation Wednesday 
96at 1 p.m. at the club house, Roxbury Memorial Park, 471 S. Roxbury Drive, 
Beverly Hills. Admission is free. For more information, call (213) 550-4761. 
</P>
<P>
 -- -- -- 
</P>
<P>
Botanist Joey Betzler is the narrator of a free slide show, "Hill Walking on 
the Northwest Coast of Southern Africa," Thursday at 7 p.m. at Recreation 
Equipment Inc., 3029 University Ave., San Diego. For more information, call 
(619) 295-7700. 
</P>
<P>
 -- -- -- 
</P>
<P>
The Bon Voyage Travel Club will present a slide show, "The Magic of Egypt," 
Sept. 15 at 7:45 p.m. in the Community Room, 9696 Wilshire Blvd., Beverly 
Hills. Admission is $5. For more information, call (213) 472-5726. 
</P>
