<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nicholas and Alexander, the two rare beaked whales that have amazed ocean 
scientists by surviving for more than a week, are continuing to hold their own 
and Alexander even ate three pounds of herring. The two had not been expected 
to survive the night when they were brought to Marine World/Africa USA animal 
park in Vallejo after beaching themselves Aug. 24 on San Francisco's Ocean 
Beach. The deep-ocean whales have been surviving on a diet of "fish shakes" 
force fed to them through tubes. Another rare whale -- a young, female pygmy 
sperm whale found beached between Santa Cruz and Monterey last week -- was 
given only a 1-in-10 chance of survival. 
</P>
</TEXT>
