<P>
Federal officers made whopping seizures on two different coasts when they found 
drugs hidden in trucks on board ships. In Columbia City, about 30 miles 
northeast of Portland, Ore., officers confiscated about 25 tons of hashish 
concealed in flatbed trucks offloaded from a docked sea vessel, the 158-foot 
