<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: MEDICAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Allergan Inc., an Irvine manufacturer of products for the care of eyes and 
skin, has made changes in its executive ranks. Richard M. Haugen has been 
appointed president of the company's optical division, which makes and markets 
contact lenses and lens-care products. Haugen replaces Donald M. Earhart, who 
resigned for personal reasons, the company said. Robert Bishop, formerly 
president of Allergan Medical Optics, the company's intraocular and surgical 
business, will replace Haugen as president of Allergan Pharmaceuticals, the 
company's prescription and over-the-counter drug business. 
</P>
