<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: MEDICAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Trimedyne Inc., the Tustin manufacturer of laser-assisted catheters to open 
blocked leg arteries, said it has received approval from the U.S. Food and Drug 
Administration to market a new laser probe. The Laserprobe SLR catheter, 3 
millimeters in diameter, is the 10th and largest probe to be marketed by 
Trimedyne, said Richard Demmer, executive vice president. 
</P>
<P>
Demmer said the probe was added to the Trimedyne product line "at the request 
of leading surgeons who asked us to develop a wider laser-heated probe to 
vaporize more plaque in the arteries." 
</P>
